</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bobby Hurley testified in Sacramento County Superior Court that he remembers 
only "bits and pieces" of the collision that almost killed him last December. 
</P>
<P>
 Hurley, the first-round draft choice of the Sacramento Kings last year, blamed 
the other motorist for the crash. Hurley said he saw no traffic when he pulled 
onto a dark road near Arco Arena after a basketball game last Dec. 12. 
</P>
<P>
 "As I was through the midst of the intersection, in a split second, I noticed 
maybe a taillight, but definitely not headlights, and I knew I was going to be 
struck then," Hurley told the court. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniel Wieland's station wagon was traveling at about 55 m.p.h. when Hurley's 
four-wheel drive vehicle turned into Wieland's path, attorneys said. Hurley, 
23, was not wearing a seat belt. He was thrown into a drainage ditch and 
suffered multiple injuries. International Sports 
</P>
<P>
 Nearly a year after it was proposed by Atlanta Olympics chief Billy Payne, 
Gov. Zell Miller approved plans for a downtown park as a festive gathering spot 
during the 1996 Games. Promising that the park will be privately funded, Gov. 
Miller said he authorized state officials to begin acquiring land and 
developing the $50-million, 60-acre Centennial Olympic Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Located in what is now a rundown section of downtown Atlanta between Georgia 
Tech and the Georgia World Congress Center, the park will be an international 
showpiece where thousands of visitors can mingle, watch the Games on huge video 
screens, buy souvenirs and eat. 
</P>
<P>
 Defending champion AC Milan, hoping to tie Real Madrid's record of six 
Champions Cup triumphs, rebounded from its upset loss to Ajax Amsterdam by 
overpowering Casino Salzburg, 3-0. . . . The International Amateur Athletic 
Federation defended its two-year suspension of sprinter Katrin Krabbe and said 
it would fight the German sprinter's lawsuit. . . . Spain opened its defense of 
the Women's World Amateur golf championship by totaling 140 to tie for the lead 
with Australia. The favored U.S. team had a first-round 141, the same as South 
Korea and France. Names in the News 
</P>
<P>
 Manager Davey Johnson, who made the Cincinnati Reds a winner again but 
couldn't win favor with owner Marge Schott, has been given permission to speak 
to the Baltimore Orioles about their managing vacancy. 
</P>
