<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; AIDS: TV ACTORS TO APPEAR AT FUND-RAISING EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tuesday's Child, a nonprofit agency for children infected with HIV, is 
observing its fifth anniversary with a series of awareness and fund-raising 
events beginning Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday, "Spinning with the Soap Opera Stars" will include a 
stationary-bicycle training session and a reception with actors from various 
shows. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization's anniversary kickoff coincides with National AIDS Awareness 
Week, Oct. 2-8; the celebration continues through Dec. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Tuesday's Child provides a range of services to benefit HIV-positive children, 
including meals, outings, rental assistance for low-income families and help 
with funeral costs. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 204-2081. 
</P>
