 SOUTH PASADENA: A Los Angeles man and an unidentified juvenile were arrested 
Tuesday morning on suspicion of auto burglary. Ruben Gonzalez, 19, and the 
juvenile were arrested at 2:41 a.m. in the 1800 block of Fremont Avenue, police 
said. They allegedly burglarized four or five cars, taking an estimated $1,000 
worth of property. Police said they recovered all of the property. 
