<P>
 After intense pressure from opponents, the City Council has tentatively 
reversed its decision earlier this year to cut the city's Planning Commission 
from seven members to five. 
</P>
<P>
 The council decided the commission should have seven members until an advisory 
measure on the 1996 municipal ballot resolves the issue. 
