<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUGUST RESTAURANT CLOSURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county Department of Health Services has the power to shut down food 
facilities for as short or as long a period of time as necessary for the owners 
to correct conditions that pose a danger to the public health. Here is a list 
of the restaurants closed during August. 
</P>
<P>
 Acapulco Mexican Restaurant -- 2060 E. Foothill Blvd., Pasadena. Closed 8/25 
to 8/26. Broken sewer line. 
</P>
<P>
 Anthony Medina -- 8215 S. Broadway, L.A. Closed 8/23 and remains closed.* No 
public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
 The Beat -- 12000 S. Western Ave., L.A. Closed 8/1 and remains closed.* No 
public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
 Bette Jean's Place -- 1513 Robertson Blvd., L.A. Closed 8/11 to 8/15. Vermin 
infestation. 
</P>
<P>
 Cafe Veracruz -- 225 West 5th St., L.A. Closed 8/2 to 8/3. Unsafe food 
temperatures, poor general sanitation, sewage system failure, vermin 
infestation, improper sanitizing or storage of multiuse utensils.  
</P>
<P>
 Carl's Jr. Restaurant -- 166 Puente Hills Mall, Industry. Closed 8/4; reopened 
same day. Sewage system failure. 
</P>
<P>
 Compton Ice Cream -- 2100 N. Long Beach Blvd., Compton. Closed 8/11 to 8/23. 
No public health permit, vermin infestation, unsafe food temperatures, improper 
sanitizing or storage of multiuse utensils. 
</P>
<P>
 El Nayarit Restaurant -- 602 1/2-604 East 7th St., L.A. Closed 8/2 to 8/5. 
Unprotected food, improper dishwashing method, no potable water supply or no 
hot water, poor general sanitation, improper sanitizing or storage of multiuse 
utensils. 
</P>
<P>
 House of Blues -- 8430 Sunset Blvd., L.A. Closed 8/12; reopened same day. No 
potable water supply or no hot water. 
</P>
<P>
 J.B. Jackson -- 8009 S. Broadway, L.A. Closed 8/15 and remains closed.* No 
public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
 Japan West -- 8009 E. Florence Ave., Downey. Closed 8/18 to 8/19. Contaminated 
food, unsafe food temperatures, improper sanitizing or storage of multiuse 
utensils. 
</P>
<P>
 Jugos Dalia -- 1467 W. Washington Blvd., L.A. Closed 8/30 and remains closed.* 
No plans submitted, no public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
 La Cocina -- 3425 East 1st St., L.A. Closed 8/9 to 8/10. Unprotected food, 
poor general sanitation, vermin infestation, improper sanitizing or storage of 
multiuse utensils. 
</P>
<P>
 Larry Parker's Beverly Hills 24-Hour Diner -- 206 S. Beverly Dr., Beverly 
Hills. Closed 8/22 to 8/23. Contaminated food, vermin infestation. 
</P>
<P>
 Latty's Restaurant -- 7903 Alix Ave., Florence. Closed 8/5 to 8/16. Vermin 
infestation, contaminated food. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Tecomates -- 5757 1/2 Lankershim Blvd., North Hollywood. Closed 8/12; 
reopened same day. No potable water supply or no hot water. 
</P>
<P>
 Mom's Donuts -- 15713 1/2 Downey Ave., Paramount. Closed 8/30 to 9/1. Vermin 
infestation, sewage system failure, improper sanitizing or storage of multiuse 
utensils. 
</P>
<P>
 MPV Seafood Restaurant -- 1412 S. Garfield Ave., Alhambra. Closed 8/1; 
reopened same day. Improper sanitizing or storage of multiuse utensils, sewage 
system failure. 
</P>
<P>
 Polly's Pie Palace -- 501 Wilshire Blvd., Santa Monica. Closed 8/11; reopened 
same day. Sewage system failure. 
</P>
<P>
 Popeye's Fried Chicken -- 1150 W. Rosecrans Ave., Gardena. Closed 8/4 to 8/8. 
No public health permit, vermin infestation, contaminated food, improper 
sanitizing or storage of multiuse utensils, poor general sanitation, improper 
dishwashing method. 
</P>
<P>
 Raji's Cuisine of India -- 637 S. Fairfax Ave., L.A. Closed 8/25 and remains 
closed.* Vermin infestation. 
</P>
<P>
 Seafood Bay -- 1240 S. Soto St., L.A. Closed 8/9 to 8/24. No potable water 
supply or no hot water, sewage system failure. 
</P>
<P>
 TG Express No. 2 -- 6056 Hollywood Blvd., L.A. Closed 8/18 to 8/23. Poor 
general sanitation. 
</P>
<P>
 Zorba's Burgers -- 510 W. Compton Blvd., Compton. Closed 8/4 to 8/9. Unsafe 
food temperatures, poor general sanitation. 
</P>
<P>
 *Remained closed as of Sept. 1.  
</P>
