<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEHIND THE SCENES: SURFRIDER GETS FORECAST FIRSTHAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSE APODACA JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The opening of another pizza joint is usually not cause for celebration, let 
alone the attention of the fashion-focused. But combine the Surfrider 
Foundation's 10th anniversary with the opening of the 10th BJ's Chicago 
Pizzeria, add in a beachwear fashion show and music from the Surftones -- and 
all the pizza you could eat -- and that warrants attention. 
</P>
<P>
 What surf gear locals will be slipping into in the coming months swept ashore 
at the downtown Huntington Beach restaurant last week. The keyword from the 
collection, shown courtesy of Huntington Surf & Sport: basics. Flannel, brush 
denim, cotton and thermal fabrics colored in olive, tan, navy, heather gray and 
black. Only red shot through as a seasonal bright in the drab fall palette.  
</P>
<P>
 But in these parts, where the weather never really gets that ugly and shorts 
are always in, the dark shades may serve as our only indication that summer is, 
at least officially, over. ROSE APODACA JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
