<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: LA MIRADA; CURBSIDE RECYCLING TO BEGIN IN JANUARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has voted unanimously to begin a curbside recycling program 
in January that will help the city comply with state environmental laws. 
</P>
<P>
 An 18-gallon bin for aluminum, newsprint, glass and plastic will be delivered 
to single-family homes, condominiums and apartment buildings with less than 
four units. Residents will not be asked to sort the materials before placing 
them in bins. 
</P>
<P>
 Monthly rates will increase $1.50 beginning in January, from $9.96 to $11.46. 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada and other cities are required by state law to recycle 25% of their 
trash in 1995. About 20% of the city's trash is currently recycled. JOHN 
CANALIS 
</P>
