<HEADLINE>
<P>
TACKLING THE LOCAL ISSUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF MEYERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unlike his happy-go-lucky colleagues on "The Dave & Bob Show," Carl Haeberle 
deals with weighty local issues: the electric company's rate increase, the city 
of Ventura's housing allotments, the county's traffic mitigation fees. 
</P>
<P>
 The hard-working Haeberle does his best to keep the conversations lively and 
balanced."If it gets boring, I shut it down," says Haeberle, whose smooth, 
stentorian voice rules the mike. 
</P>
<P>
 Replacing such a local institution as the late Frank Haines isn't easy, and 
Haeberle admits "it was scary" when he went on the air last November, a month 
after Haines died. 
</P>
<P>
 A radio veteran, spending the last five years at KGO in San Francisco, 
Haeberle gave himself a crash course in local history and culture and now 
handles hometown issues like a native. 
</P>
<P>
 "Carl has done a sensational job," says KVEN president and general manager 
David Loe. "Frank was a tough act to follow, but Carl's building a bigger and 
bigger audience every day." JEFF MEYERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Sidebar 
</P>
</TYPE>
