<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOBBITT GETS 30 DAYS ON SECOND CHARGE OF BATTERING GIRLFRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Wayne Bobbitt was convicted of a second domestic battery charge Tuesday 
and ordered to serve 30 days in jail by a judge who called him a bully. 
</P>
<P>
 Kristina Elliott testified that her former fiance twisted her arm behind her 
back and threw her against an apartment wall May 6. 
</P>
<P>
 Bobbitt served 12 days of a 15-day sentence this month for battering Elliott 
in a separate incident. 
</P>
<P>
 "One thing is apparent and that is that you are a bully," Municipal Judge Ron 
D. Parraguirre said. "I don't know how we're going to get this across to you 
that this is unacceptable behavior." 
</P>
<P>
 Bobbitt gained national attention when his wife, Lorena Bobbitt, sliced off 
his penis last year, saying he had sexually assaulted her. The penis was 
surgically reattached. Lorena Bobbitt was found not guilty by reason of 
insanity and filed for divorce. 
</P>
<P>
 Parraguirre sentenced Bobbitt to 90 days in jail with 60 days suspended and 
placed him on probation for one year, during which time he must abstain from 
alcohol and receive counseling. Bobbitt's attorney, Michael Stein, said he will 
appeal. 
</P>
