COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 5 DISPLACED AS FIRE DAMAGES DUPLEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire in a duplex Wednesday morning damaged both units, displacing five 
residents but injuring no one. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators say the cause of the blaze in the 300 block of East Orangewood 
Avenue may have been a malfunctioning dryer in a garage attached to the units. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire began about 9 a.m. and spread quickly through the attics of both 
units. Damaged was estimated at $30,000 to the building and $40,000 to 
contents, Battalion Chief Benny Ramirez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents in one unit were home when the fire started but got out, Ramirez 
said. No one was home at the other unit, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters controlled the blaze in about 15 minutes, Ramirez said.KEN 
ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
