<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLORES TO RIDE FLYING SENSATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ROBLEDO, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Flores, the Fairplex meeting's leading rider, has been named to ride 
Flying Sensation in Saturday's $100,000 Pomona Derby at Fairplex Park in 
Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
 Alex Solis was originally recruited to ride the son of Flying Paster after 
Solis committed to ride trainer Don Warren's horses Thursday, Friday and 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 But when Harry Hacek, Solis' agent, said the jockey couldn't ride the first 
two days, Warren switched jockeys.  
</P>
<P>
 Flying Sensation hasn't won a race since the California Cup Juvenile almost a 
year ago, but he demonstrated a liking for the small track last year with a 
second-place finish to Individual Style in the Gate For Glory Stakes. 
</P>
<P>
 Notes 
</P>
<P>
 Katilac Ofthestars, last in a nine-horse field the first time around the 
track, rallied under Gary Baze to beat The Jody Grind by two lengths in the 
$50,000 Black Swan Stakes on Wednesday. Pascali, with Justin Vitek aboard, was 
third. . . . The Super Derby from Louisiana Downs, which includes trainer Dick 
Mandella's Soul Of The Matter, will be simulcast at Fairplex Park on Saturday. 
. . . Magical Maiden, third in the 1992 Breeders' Cup Distaff, drew the No. 1 
post position in a five-horse field in today's $100,000 Las Madrinas Handicap. 
</P>
