<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UCI RALLIES FOR SOCCER VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine rallied from a late two-goal deficit and beat Loyola Marymount in 
overtime, 4-3, in a nonconference men's soccer game Wednesday at Loyola. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior Adel Afkarian scored two goals in a 13-minutes span, including the 
game-winner seven minutes into overtime for the Anteaters (7-1), who won their 
sixth consecutive game. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola (2-5) took a 3-1 lead when Shane Gallagher and William Gast scored in 
the 73rd and 74th minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 P.J. Polowski scored his eighth goal of the season in the 77th minute and 
Afkarian tied the score in the 84th minute. Loyola didn't take a shot in 
overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 UC San Diego 1, Southern California College 0 -- Chris Fong scored in the 
fourth minute for host UC San Diego. Goalie Brent Rogers had five saves for SCC 
(4-5), which outshot San Diego, 13-6. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 2, Loyola Marymount 1 -- Jenni Tanaka scored 33 minutes into the 
game to give the Anteaters (5-4) a 2-1 lead. Shawna Berke tied the score, 1-1, 
when she took an indirect free kick from Nicole Kelly and scored nine minutes 
into the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Judey Petix scored after a back-heel pass on a free kick by Trisha Abe, 
formerly of Mater Dei, five minutes into the game for Loyola (1-5-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara 3, UC Irvine 0 -- Heather Collins had 18 kills for the host 
Gauchos (12-0, 4-0). Popi Edwards had 13 kills for the Anteaters (2-10, 1-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 3, The Master's 2 -- Lori Fuller had 24 kills and Shawna Parkinson had 
14 for host Chapman (14-3), which won, 7-15, 9-15, 15-10, 15-9, 15-5. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 3, CS San Bernardino 0 -- Celeste Young had 18 
kills and Simon Burgesmier had 11 for the Vanguards (12-4), who won, 15-9, 
15-5, 15-10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
