<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAVATA TO COACH AT WOODBRIDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sam Favata, a former Cal State Fullerton baseball player, was hired Wednesday 
as Woodbridge's baseball coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Favata, who played in the Milwaukee Brewers' organization, replaces Vince 
Brown, who left after two seasons with the Warriors. 
</P>
<P>
 Favata was the head coach at Edgewood (now West Covina) High School four 
years, from 1985-88, where he won three league championships and finished with 
a 76-29 record. 
</P>
<P>
 "I missed coaching after my four years at Edgewood," Favata said. "I was 
looking for the right opportunity to get back into a team situation." 
</P>
<P>
 Favata, who played second base, worked recently as director of the "Better 
Baseball 4 Kids" Clinic and was an instructor at local hitting and base-running 
clinics. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown led the Warriors to a Sea View League title in 1993 and a fourth-place 
finish in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
