<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Koll Builds in China: Koll China Real Estate Co. is developing a $175-million 
office and convention center in Beijing. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is one of the first for Koll China, a division of Koll Co. that 
was formed late last year to lead the Newport Beach developer's operations in 
China. 
</P>
<P>
 The futuristic-looking Beijing High Tech Center project will include 500,000 
square feet of office space, 400 apartments and 75,000 square feet of retail 
area. It will also have a 140,000-square-foot convention center. 
</P>
<P>
 "It will be the living room for the high-tech industry in China," said Kenneth 
Munkacy, president of Koll China. "Right now there is just no space in that 
area. There is no good showroom space or office space." 
</P>
<P>
 Under construction in the northwest portion of the Haidian district of 
Beijing, the office tower will be the centerpiece of the district, Munkacy 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Koll China said it has several other deals in the works in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
