</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Platinum Software Corp.: The company said it has raised $13.76 million from a 
private placement of 2.49 million shares of preferred stock. 
</P>
<P>
 A group of investors led by Kleiner, Perkins, Caufield & Byers of San 
Francisco and New Enterprise Associates of Menlo Park now controls 14% of 
Irvine-based Platinum's stock. Arthur J. Marks, a principal at New Enterprise, 
and L. John Doerr, general partner of Kleiner Perkins, were given seats on 
Platinum's board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 In Wednesday's trading on the Nasdaq market, Platinum's stock closed at $10.56 
a share, up 93 cents. 
