<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Comarco Inc.: The Yorba Linda engineering company said Wednesday that its 
contract with the Navy to provide engineering services at the Naval Air Warfare 
Center at China Lake has been extended through November. 
</P>
<P>
 Comarco said the Navy is likely to extend its contract in two-month intervals 
through May. Each extension is worth about $2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The firm also said it has been readmitted to competition for a five-year, 
$400-million contract to provide engineering services at China Lake and at the 
Point Mugu Naval Station. In August, Comarco had been eliminated from 
competition for the contract, which is expected to be awarded by May. 
</P>
